This paper presents a method for quantized inference of neural networks, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, given that the paper focuses on the performance of the method across a variety of applications and neural network architectures, as well as its ability to enable traditional hardware platforms to realize inference speedups, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Other possible categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language), as these sub-fields are also relevant to the topic of neural network inference.
